mpeg_encode
-------------------------------------------
This directory contains the freely distributed Berkeley MPEG-1 Video
Encoder and conversion utilities.  The encoder implements the standard 
described in the ISO/IEC International Standard 11172-2.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.15-15
  libjpeg62-6b-12

Build requirements:
  binutils-20080624-2
  cygport-0.4.2-1
  gcc-core-3.4.4-3
  make-3.81-1
  sed-4.1.5-2

Canonical homepage:
  http://bmrc.berkeley.edu/research/mpeg/mpeg_encode.html

Canonical download:
  ftp://mm-ftp.cs.berkeley.edu/pub/multimedia/mpeg/encode/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack mpeg_encode-1.5b-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./mpeg_encode-1.5b-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/mpeg_encode-1.5b-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/mpeg_encode-1.5b-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

  /usr/bin/eyuvtojpeg.exe
  /usr/bin/jmovie2jpeg.exe
  /usr/bin/movieToVid.exe
  /usr/bin/mpeg_demux.exe
  /usr/bin/mpeg_encode.exe
  /usr/share/doc/mpeg_encode-1.5b/ANNOUNCE
  /usr/share/doc/mpeg_encode-1.5b/BUGS
  /usr/share/doc/mpeg_encode-1.5b/Changes
  /usr/share/doc/mpeg_encode-1.5b/COPYRIGHT
  /usr/share/doc/mpeg_encode-1.5b/EXTENSIONS
  /usr/share/doc/mpeg_encode-1.5b/INPUT.FORMAT
  /usr/share/doc/mpeg_encode-1.5b/INSTALL
  /usr/share/doc/mpeg_encode-1.5b/NOTES
  /usr/share/doc/mpeg_encode-1.5b/README
  /usr/share/doc/mpeg_encode-1.5b/README.convert
  /usr/share/doc/mpeg_encode-1.5b/README.mtv
  /usr/share/doc/mpeg_encode-1.5b/TODO
  /usr/share/man/man1/mpeg_encode.1.gz

------------------

Port Notes:

----- version 1.5b-3 -----
Patches from Gentoo to use system jpeg and other issues.
eyuvtoppm/ppmtoeyuv now provided by netpbm.

----- version 1.5b-2 -----
Includes patch for CAN-2005-3115 from the Gentoo Security Team.

----- version 1.5b-1 -----
Initial release for Cygwin.
Includes patches from the Gentoo Linux ebuild.


Cygwin port maintained by:
http://cygwinports.dotsrc.org/
